{
 "name": "RPlog_Brig_-_Day_Three",
 "title": "Brig: Day Three",
 "summary": "On the third day of confinement aboard the Inquisitor, Lynae Caiton and Antoine Dareus are briefly lowered for a wash and fresh prison garb when Davyd arrives and lets them stay on the floor. Dareus, having repeatedly torn his shoulder back into joint each time they are strung up, screams as Lynae tends the dislocation, and the two trade weary gallows humor about replacement surgery and what little futures await them once this is over, before the stormtroopers hoist them back up. The scene then shifts to a separate interrogation cell where CompForce has moved Dareus alone. Stripped of rank and weapons, Lieutenant Maris Becton conducts a harsh interrogation, slapping and goading him as she demands the full timeline of the conspiracy. Dareus recounts how the supposedly dead Grand Admiral Danik Kreldin recruited him on Caspar, revealing a sweeping plan to seize the throne by turning the Jedi against the Sith, and explains that Lynae served as the voice of reason throughout, exposing the plan's folly. Maris scoffs at Kreldin's delusions, presses for details, and finally warns Dareus to eat because his next questioning will be far less pleasant before sealing the cell behind her.",
